<TITLE> Businessmen pledge aid to Sidr victims </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 20 (bdnews24.com) -- Businessmen Tuesday pledged to assist the government in its efforts to cope with the destruction and devastation caused to life and property by mega-cyclone Sidr. Business organisations will inform the government Sunday about the accurate figure of cash and emergency relief materials. Businessmen assured food and disaster management adviser Tapan Chowdhury of providing cash and relief materials at a meeting during which the adviser called for assistance. "Work on disbursement of relief materials is underway in the cyclone-ravaged areas. We held a meeting to involve the businessmen in relief activities. The businessmen will give the accurate figure of money Sunday," Tapan told reporters. The BGMEA confirmed that it would donate one lakh sweaters, two lakh shirts and trousers while the BKMEA said it would give five lakh vests and T-shirts. The delegates said that they would also try to gather and distribute more relief materials under the assistance of local district chambers. The relief materials will be distributed in the selected areas in line with necessity. bdnews24
